---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config/site';
---
<Layout
  title={`About | ${SITE.name}`}
  description="About Compute Current, an AI infrastructure intelligence publication for operators, investors, cloud capacity teams, data center developers, and infrastructure strategists."
  canonicalPath="/about/"
>
  <main class="policy-shell">
    <a class="back-link" href="/">Intelligence board</a>
    <article class="policy-page">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>Compute Current tracks the constraints behind the AI buildout.</h1>
      <p class="policy-lede">
        Compute Current is an AI infrastructure intelligence publication tracking power, cooling, semiconductors, cloud capacity, data centers, capital flows, and policy risk.
      </p>

      <section>
        <h2>What We Cover</h2>
        <p>
          Coverage areas include power and grid, data centers, cooling, semiconductors, cloud capacity, capital flows, policy and siting risk, and enterprise infrastructure.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Who We Serve</h2>
        <p>
          The publication is built for data center operators, colocation and wholesale teams, hyperscaler capacity groups, infrastructure investors, power stakeholders, silicon and networking suppliers, enterprise infrastructure buyers, and policy professionals.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>What We Do Not Try To Be</h2>
        <p>
          Compute Current is not a generic AI blog. We do not force weakly related AI news into an infrastructure frame, and we do not publish long-form generated memos from sources that fail extraction quality checks.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Reader Promise</h2>
        <p>
          Every full memo is intended to answer what changed, why it matters for AI infrastructure, who benefits, who is exposed, and what bottleneck or decision point readers should watch next.
        </p>
      </section>

      <nav class="policy-link-row" aria-label="Transparency pages">
        <a href="/editorial-policy/">Editorial Policy</a>
        <a href="/methodology/">Methodology</a>
        <a href="/ai-disclosure/">AI-assisted Disclosure</a>
        <a href="/pricing/">Pricing</a>
        <a href="/advertise/">Advertise</a>
      </nav>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
